1527 1528 Section 11 / Cardiopulmonary System This chapter will next describe the clinical features of feline cardiomyopathies and the therapy of related complications. Following this is a consideration of canine DCM and arrhythmogenic cardiomyopathy. Overview and Pathophysiology of Feline HCM • Feline idiopathic HCM is characterized by hypertrophy and thickening of the left ventricle unexplained by congenital heart disease, systemic hypertension, or an endocrinopathy. • The condition is genetic in a number of feline breeds, including the Maine coon cat, Persian cat, and the Ragdoll. Thus far, one sarcomeric mutation has been identified. 